description:
SOURCES ARE BELOW.

THE CHARITY  I strongly endorse is called ASRI. It’s a hospital in Borneo that provides affordable health care to villages on the edge of a national park in return for a pledge not to cut down trees, The pledges are monitored,a nd the result is a dramatic decrease in deforestation rates and an increase in the health of the local population. The founders are hoping to spread the idea to other countries. (see https://psmag.com/social-justice/save-the-trees-well-save-your-life-46121 for an explanation of their work.)

  You can make a donation by bank transfer here…
   http://www.alamsehatlestari.org/donate/

…or if you want to do it online they also have a US fundraising arm called Health in Harmony:
 https://healthinharmony.org/donate/
